items.sentence: Tom and Mary stared into each other\'s eyes.
I told myself I\'d never be able to do that.
I want everything that\'s not working fixed.
Tom kept looking at you. Didn\'t you notice?
Tom knew that Mary wasn\'t going to be busy.
Tom knew that Mary wasn\'t going to do that.
Tom is very worried about what might happen.
Did you know that your brake lights are out?
Did your high school have a basketball team?
Do both Tom and Mary still enjoy doing that?
Do you allow your children to eat ice cream?
Do you have a nail file that I could borrow?
I forwarded the schedule you sent me to Tom.
Didn\'t you know Tom couldn\'t speak French?
Tom was still in Boston this time last year.
Can you please tell me how much it\'s worth?
Can you remember what we\'re supposed to do?
Tom, could you shut up for just ten seconds?
Was Tom the one who told you not to do that?
We ate corn on the cob for dinner yesterday.
